A) Create Oracle Virtual box Virtual Machines
 1. CentOS 8.4 
 2. RHEL 7.9 

 https://www.virtualbox.org/

 - CentOs is the controller machine
 - RHEL is the Target machine

B) Install Mobaxterm for the Remote SSH Connection to the Controller and for the file transfer
 https://mobaxterm.mobatek.net/

C) Configure Visual studio code as the Development Environment 
 https://code.visualstudio.com/


 Installed Ansible extension to work with Ansible Playbook
 https://docs.ansible.com/ansible/latest/installation_guide/intro_installation.html
 
 Install YAML Extension to check for the Syntax errors while writing the playbook
 https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=redhat.vscode-yaml

 Install the SFTP Extension to connect to the Control machine to transfer the file to  the controller machine (Local to Remote)
 https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=liximomo.sftp
 
 SFTP CONFIG FILE:
 sftp.json
 {
    "name": "Name for the connection",
    "host": "xxx.xx.xxx.xx",
    "protocol": "sftp",
    "port": 22,
    "username": "osboxes",
    "password": "osboxes.org",
    "remotePath": "/home/osboxes/Desktop/ansible",
    "uploadOnSave": true
}